                <c02 id="ref137" level="subseries">
                    <did>
                        <unittitle>U.S. Military Observers in Yenan, China collected reports microfilm reel,</unittitle>
                        <container id="cid5151001" type="microfilm" label="Microfilm Reel">1</container>
                        <unitdate>1944-1971 (bulk 1944-1946) </unitdate>
                    </did>
                    <scopecontent id="ref138">
                        <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
                        <p>Includes four volumes of collected administrative and other reports concerning the Yenan Observer Group (Code Name: Dixie Mission; File No. Geog V China 334--Dixie Mission). The Yenan Observer Group arrived in Yenan, China, on July 22, 1944. The volumes were regraded unclassified by the Secretary of the Army in 1971.</p>
                        <p>Volume 1 index: Army Ground Forces Resources Technical Staff; Air Ground Aid Service Section, American--Communist Relations, Colonel Dave Barrett's Reports, Miscellaneous Correspondence, Maps, Charts, Foreign Economics Administration, Ambassador Patrick J. Hurley</p>
                        <p>Volume 2 index: Illustrations, Maps of areas, Interviews with Lt. George I. Nakamura, Nationalist--Communist Relations, Naval Intelligence, Operations Conditions, Order of Battle Section, Office of Strategic Services (OSS), Office of War Information (OWI), Personalities Involved, Propaganda</p>
                        <p>Volume 3 index: Preliminary Story, Tenth Weather Squadron Detachment, Twentieth Bomber Command, Wind-Up Of Mission, Colonel Yeaton, Yensig Section (Proposed), china Theater Political History (by Fenton Keyes), G-5 Clandestine Branch History Excerpts</p>
                        <p>Volume 4 is not indexed.</p>
                    </scopecontent>
                </c02>
            </c01>
